      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/man-la-yahduruhu-al-faqih:1:33:26",
      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/1/33/671",
      "text": [
        " شَكٍّ مِنَ اَلْوَقْتِ وَ قَبْلَ اَلْوَقْتِ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.671 - Abu Ja'far, Imam Muhammad ibn Ali Al-Baqir (as), said:\n\"It is more beloved to me to pray after the time (for prayer) has passed than to pray while I am in doubt about whether it is the correct time or before the time (for prayer) has entered.\""
        ]
      }
    },
